definitions.definition: To fool ; to cause to believe something untrue; to deceive .
examples: You tried to trick me when you said that house was underpriced.
I was once tricked into believing I had left my phone in the locker.

definitions.definition: To draw (as contrasted with to blazon , which is to describe in words).
To dress ; to decorate ; to adorn fantastically; often followed by up , off , or out .
To engage in prostitution or casual sex .
